Say (O Muhammad SAW): "I have been forbidden to worship those whom you invoke besides Allah." Say: "I do not follow your desires, lest I have gone astray, and I have gone astray, and I will not be among the guided."
Say: 'I am only a clear proof from my Lord, and you deny the truth. You do not hasten what you hasten to hasten. The decision is only with Allah. He relates the truth. He is the Best of deciders."
Say: "If you were impatient for what you wish to hasten, it would have been settled between me and me." And Allah knows best the wrong-doers.
He knows the keys of the unseen, the keys of the unseen. He knows what is in the earth and the sea. No leaf is He, and He knows it, but He knows the earth and the earth, but there is nothing but a grain in the earth, but there is nothing smaller in a clear Book.
It is He who recalls you in the night, and He knows what you earn of day, then He raises you to die, so that you may be returned to Him. Then to Him you will return, and He will inform you of what you used to do.
He is the Conqueror over His servants, and He sends guardians over you. When death approaches you, Our messengers call him to death, and they are not neglectful.
Then they are returned to Allah, their Lord, the True. His is the judgement, and He is the swiftest of reckoners.
Say, "Who rescues you from the darkness of the land and the sea, when you call upon Him and call upon Him whatever you call upon Him?"
Say, "It is God who delivers you from every evil and from every distress from you, and you associate others besides Him."
Say: "He is Able to send down upon you a power of your hands or from beneath them from His feet, or to make you taste one another factions and make you taste one another. See how We explain Our signs to you, so that they may understand."
And you disbelieve in the truth, and it is the truth. Say: "I am not a guardian over you."
For every soul is a finality, and you will soon know.
And when you see those who gossip in Our revelations, they turn away from you, but if they turn away to you, they do not dispute with one another. And if you forget you, then do not be of the unjust.
For those who fear the duty of Allah, there is no sin for them, so that they may fear.
And (as for) those who have set their religion as a sport and a sport, and the life of this world beguiled the life of this world, and warn the Qur'an, and warn the Qur'an. And they shall not be able to be a ransom for them, and they shall not be able to protect a ransom from Allah. They are the ones who have no power of a painful punishment.
Say: 'Shall I not bring him any other than Allah, or He will not harm it for us, nor will he harm nor harm you, if you are returned to us?" And they are in the hearts of those whose hearts see them, so that they should say to them, "What is the hearts of the people who have been guided." Say, "We have been commanded to follow the guidance of God, and we have been commanded to submit."
And to establish the prayer and fear Him, and He is the Day of Judgment.
It is He who created the heavens and the earth in truth. He will say, "Be," His word is the Truth. His is the sovereignty on the Day when the trumpet will be blown. He is the All-Knower, the All-knowing.
And (remember) when Abraham said to his father Azar, "Do you take idols as gods? I see you, you, and your people, in manifest error.
And thus We gave him the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, that he might be of the believers.
Then when the night covered him, he saw a star rising. He said, "This is my Lord." And when it set, he said, “I do not love those who do not love.”
Then, when he saw the moon rising, he said, "This is my Lord.” But when it set, he said, “If my Lord does not guide me, I will surely have followed the people who are astray.”
When he saw the sun rising, he said, "This is my Lord." But when it set, he said, “My people, I am quit of what you associate with Him.”
I have turned my face towards Him who has created the heavens and the earth, and I am not one of those who associate others with Allah.
His people argued with him. He said, "Do you argue with me about God? He has guided me to me. I do not fear Him as I associate you with Him. My Lord comprehends all things in knowledge. Will you not take heed?
And how should I fear that which ye associate beside Allah, and that ye have not associated with Him any warrant which He has not sent down to you any warrant? Is it any of the two parties?
Those who believe and do not mix their faith, for them shall be security, and they are rightly guided.
And this is Our argument that We gave to Abraham his brother, so We will raise him degrees in degrees. Lo! thy Lord is Wise, Wise.
And We gave him Isaac and Jacob, and We guided them. And We guided Noah before Noah, and his descendants, and Job, Job and Job, Job and Aaron. Thus do We reward the righteous.
And Zakariya and John and John and Elias, and each of them was righteous.
And Ishmael and Elisha, and Lot, and Lot, and We gave them a great reward.
And of their fathers and their descendants, and their brethren, and We chose them and guided them to the right path.
That is the guidance of Allah, He guides whomever He wills of His servants. If they had associated anything other than Him, they would have been annulled.
They are the ones whom We have given the Book and wisdom, and prophethood, and prophethood. And We have made a sign to a people who do not believe in it.
Those are the ones whom Allah has guided. So follow their guidance. Say, "I do not ask you any wage for this. It is only a reminder for the worlds."
And what Allah has not made those who do not say, "He has not sent down any revelation." They say, "He has sent down a Book." Say, "It has been revealed to you that the Book has been sent down to the people, and He has given it to you as He wills. He knows what you do not know.
And this is the Book which We have sent down, confirming what We have revealed before it, confirming what was before it, and those who believe in it, and those who believe in the Hereafter, and those who believe in the Hereafter, and those who believe.
And who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah, or says, "It is revealed to me, or to it has been revealed to me." Say, "It is God who has sent down the Book." And if you see them, the angels will say, "This is your hands." And if you see it, the angels will say, "This is your disgrace. This is the punishment for those who disobey Allah."
And indeed you are returned to Us, as We created you the first time, and We have given you what We had been given you. And We do not see you with those whom you claimed in God. Indeed, you claimed with those whom you claimed with God.
It is Allah who splits the grain-stone, the date-stone, the date-stone. He brings forth the living from the dead, and He brings forth the living from the dead. That is Allah, then how are you turned away?
It is He Who breaks the dawn, and He made the night for rest and the sun and the moon for calculation. He is the All-mighty, the All-knowing.
And He it is Who hath set the stars for you, that you may be guided by the darkness of the darkness of the darkness of the sea and the sea. We have detailed the revelations for people who understand.
And He it is Who has produced you from a single soul, then He has appointed for you a place of sojourning and a place of storage. Verily We have detailed for a people who understand.
It is He who sends down water from the sky, and We bring it grow with every kind of vegetation, and We bring forth thereby kinds of vegetation grow to grow. And We bring forth gardens of date-palms, with clusters of date trees, and olives, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates. In this are signs for people who believe.
And they ascribe up partners to Allah, and He has created them, and He created them, and they impute to Him sons and daughters. Glory be to Him! High be He above what they associate.
He is the Originator of the heavens and the earth. How can He have a son when He has no consort? He has created everything and He has knowledge of all things.
He is the Lord of your Lord, there is no god but He. So worship Him, and worship Him. He is the Guardian over all things.
No eyes can grasp Him, but He perceives what He wills. He is the Subtle, the Expert.
Indeed, there has come to you from your Lord. So whoever sees it, it is for his own soul; and whoever is blind, it is only for his own soul; and I am not a guardian over you.
Thus do We explain Our revelations to them, and they say: "We have studied," and that We may make it clear to the people who know.
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord. There is no god but He; and turn away from those who turn away from Allah.
And if Allah had pleased, they would not have associated Him; and We have not made you a guardian over them, and thou art not over them a manager.
Do not insult those whom they call upon besides Allah, lest they insult the hostility of ignorance. Thus We have made attractive to every nation their deeds. We have made their deeds attractive to them. Then their Lord will inform them of what they used to do.
And they swear by Allah with their solemn oaths that if there came to them a sign, they would believe in it. Say: 'Signs are with Allah." And what will make you realize that they have come to believe, then they would not believe?
And their hearts and their eyes will come to them, but they will not believe in it, but We will leave them in their insolence, and We shall wander blindly in their trespasses.
And if We had sent down the angels to them, and the dead are gathered to them, and We have gathered them all together before them, they would have believed in it. Even they would not believe unless Allah had willed, but most of them are ignorant.
Thus is how We have made every prophet a prophet from among mankind, and among the jinn, the devils, inspiring them with inspiring themselves. And if your Lord willed, they would not have done it. So leave them, and follow what they fabricate.
And those who do not believe in the Hereafter, so that the hearts of their hearts may incline to them, and that they may be pleased.
Say, “Shall I seek a judge other than Allah, while it is He Who has revealed to you the Book?” And those who gave the Book know that it has been revealed to you from your Lord. So do not be of the doubters.
And the Word of your Lord is the truth and the Last Day. No one can change His words. He is the All-hearing, the All-knowing.
And if most of the people of the earth, they would lead you astray from Allah. They follow nothing but conjecture, and they are merely conjecturing.
Indeed your Lord knows best those who stray from His path, and He knows best those who are guided.
So eat of that which Allah hath mentioned, and that which is in the name of Allah eat.
And what is the matter with you that you do not eat that the name of Allah has been mentioned to you, and that which has been forbidden to you, except that which is forbidden to you? They lead only astray from their own desires. Indeed your Lord knows best the transgressors.
Forsake the sin and the sin. Those who commit sin shall be recompensed for what they used to do.
And do not eat that which is in the name of Allah has not been pronounced. Indeed, it is a sin. And the devils inspire their friends to argue with you. If you obey them, you will surely be idolaters.
Is he who was dead, and We gave him life, and We have made him a light of which he walks to one people? Is he equal to one who can bring out the darkness of darkness? Thus the unbelievers have been made fair fair seeming to them.
And thus We have made every city a town in its city, so that they may plot therein. And they do not plot except themselves except themselves, and they do not know.
When a sign comes to them, they say: "We will not believe in it until we do not believe in the Book." Allah knows best where He has given to His servants. The evil-doers will be seized by severe punishment.
So Allah guides to whomever He wills, He expands his breast to Islam. And He makes whomever He wishes to go astray, as if he were climbing to the sky. So He makes it to go astray in the sky, so that they do not believe.
This is the path of your Lord, a straight path. We have detailed for the people who understand.
Their abode will be the Garden of Paradise, and He will be their Protector. He is the Best of reward.
On the day when He will gather them all together, He will say: "Company, the people of jinn." And the group of them will say: "Our Lord, we have enjoyed us from a single term." They will say, "Our Lord, we have enjoyed us from a single term." He will say, "Your Lord, the Fire, the Fire." He will say: "This is your dwelling, and your Lord is Wise."
And thus do We make the wrong-doers among the wrong-doers, because of what they used to earn.
O ye assembly of jinn and mankind! Did there not come to you apostles from among yourselves, relating to you My verses and warning you to warn My signs? They will say: We bear witness against ourselves and the Day of Resurrection? They shall say, "We bear witness against ourselves." And the life of this world is deluded against them.
That is because your Lord does not destroy the towns unjustly while they are unaware of their ignorance.
And for them is degrees for what they have done, and your Lord is not unaware of what they do.
And your Lord is the Self-sufficient, the All-merciful. If He wills, He could have put you away, and He will replace you for you as He wills, and He will raise you to another people as a descendants.
Indeed that which you have been promised will come to pass, and you cannot frustrate it.
Say: 'O my people! Work according to your station. I am acting to your station. You will know that you will know in the Hereafter. The wrongdoers will not prosper.
And they assign to Allah a share of the cattle and the cattle which He has created for them, and they say, "This is for God." And they say, "This is for Allah." And when they associate their associates, it is not a thing of Allah, and that which they associate is with Allah.
And thus their associates have made the killing of the polytheists, and their children made their children, and made them their religion and their religion. And if Allah had willed, they would not have done it. So leave them with their fabrications, and follow them.
And they say: "These cattle and crops are forbidden, and such not eat what We have forbidden for him." They are forbidden by cattle, and they are forbidden by cattle, and cattle, and cattle, and cattle, and cattle. They are not fabricating lies against Allah.
And they say: "What is in the bellies of cattle is reserved for our males, and for our wives, and our wives are forbidden." But if it is stillborn, they shall have shares it. He will punish them for their attribution. He is All-knowing, All-knowing.
Lost are they who have killed their children foolishly, without knowledge, without knowledge, and has forbidden what Allah has provided for them, inventing lies against Allah. They have gone astray, and they are not guided.
It is He who produces gardens, trellised, and untrellised, and palm-trees, and the date-palm-palm-trees, and olives, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and pomegranates, and unlike, and unlike, and unlike, but eat of its fruit; and do not exceed the fruit of its fruit. Indeed, He does not love the wasteful.
And of the cattle, there are some of burden, and the flesh of the burden. Eat of what Allah has provided for you and do not follow the footsteps of Satan. Indeed, he is an open enemy to you.
Eight, and the pair of sheep. Say: 'Is it the two males He has forbidden, or the two females, or the two females, or what the wombs of the two females contain? Tell me with knowledge, if you are truthful.”
And the pair of camels, and the pair of oxen. Say: 'Is it the two males He has forbidden, or the two females, or what the wombs of the two females contain? Or, when Allah commanded you, you would have been charged to you?" And he who invents a lie against Allah, who lead him astray from knowledge? Indeed, Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people.
Say: 'I have been forbidden to eat that which has been revealed to me to eat of what is forbidden to eat, except carrion, pork, pork, pork, the flesh of swine, the flesh of swine, and the flesh of swine, and the flesh of God. And whoever is constrained with necessity, not desiring it, and transgress that Allah is Forgiving, Merciful.
And to those who are Jews, We forbade the animal with claws, and the fat of them, and the fat of them, and the fat of what adheres to their backs, except what adheres to their backs, or what adheres to their backs, and that which was mixed to them, We seized them because of their sins; and We are the truthful.
But if they accuse you, say: "Your Lord is the Lord of Mercy and mercy." And none will not be averted from the sinners.
The idolaters will say, "Had Allah willed, we would not have worshipped anything besides Him, nor we nor our fathers, nor would we have forbidden anything.” Likewise, those who lived before them cried lies to Our punishment. Say, "Have you bring any proof to us? You follow only surmise. You follow nothing but conjecture. You merely follow conjecture.
Say: "The Book is only for Allah. If He willed, He could have guided you to the right path."
Say (O Muhammad SAW): "Bring your witnesses (i.e. the Jews), and those who testify against Allah, that they testify not." And do not bear witness with them, and do not follow those who deny Our Ayat (proofs, evidences, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, etc.), and do not follow the Hereafter, and do not follow the Hereafter with their Lord.
Say: "Your Lord has made lawful to you what you have made unlawful. Do not associate anything with Him, and do not be your partner to your parents. Do not kill your wealth and your children. Do not kill your wealth. We do not be grieved. Do not kill your wealth, but do not kill your property. This is best for you.
And do not approach the property of the orphan except the property of the orphan until he reaches maturity. And give full measure and weight with justice. We do not burden any soul except a soul. We do not burden any soul except it. Do you speak to yourselves, if you speak.
And that it is My path that is straight, so follow it, and do not follow any paths other than it, lest they may lead you away from His path. That is He that you may fear.
Then We gave Moses the Book as a favour for him, and explaining everything in detail, and guidance, and mercy, and mercy, that they may believe in their Lord.
And this is a blessed Book which We have revealed, so follow it and follow it, so that you may receive mercy.
Lest you will say, "The Book has been sent down to two two parties before us, and we have been heedless of their study."
Or lest you should say, "If the Book had been sent down to us, we would surely have been guided than them.” Indeed, there has come to you a clear proof from your Lord, and a guidance and mercy and mercy. Who is more unjust than he who denies the signs of God and turns away from them. We turn away from those who turn away from Our signs.
Are they waiting for the angels, or the angels come to them, or your Lord’s signs comes to you, or the sign of your Lord comes to you, but that the Day of Resurrection comes to him, except that no one of it comes to faith before his faith? Say, "Wait, we too are waiting."
Those who split their religion into sects and sects, there is no concern of them. Their affair is only with Allah. He will inform them of what they used to do.
Whoever brings a good deed, it shall be tenfold for it; and whoever brings an evil deed, it shall be recompensed for it, and they shall not be wronged.
Say: 'My Lord has guided me to a straight path, the religion of Abraham, the upright, the upright, and he was not one of the polytheists.
Say: "My prayer and my sacrifice, and my living, and my living, and my Lord, the Lord of the Worlds.
He has no partner; and I have been commanded to be the first, and I am the first of those who submit.
Say: 'Shall I seek a god other than Allah, while He is the Lord of all things? No soul earns its soul. No soul earns the burden of another soul, and no bearer of burden shall bear another burden. Then your Lord will inform you about what you used to differ.
And He it is Who hath appointed you on the earth, and hath raised some of you ranks over others, that He may test you in what He has given you. Lo! thy Lord is swift in retribution, and He is Forgiving, Merciful.
