(This is) the Book which We have revealed to you (O Muhammad SAW), so that you may warn it from your heart, and that it may be no crookedness for the believers.
Follow what has been revealed to you from your Lord, and do not follow any other other than Him. Little do you take heed.
And how many a town have We destroyed! Our punishment came upon them by night, while they slept.
Then, when Our punishment came to them, they said, "Indeed, we were wrongdoers."
Then We shall question those who have been sent to Our Messenger, and We shall question the messengers.
Then We shall narrate them with knowledge, and We are not absent.
The weighing on that Day is the Truth; and those whose scales are heavy—they are the successful.
And those whose scales are light, it are they who have lost their souls, because they used to deny Our signs.
And indeed We have established you in the earth and made for you a livelihood for you. Little thanks ye thanks.
We created you, then We shaped you, then We said to the angels, "Prostrate to Adam." Prostrate, "Prostrate to Adam," they prostrated themselves, but he was not of those who prostrated.
He said, “What prevented you that you did not prostrate to what I commanded you?” He said, “I am better than he. You created me from fire, and You created him from clay.”
(Allah) said: "Get down from it! It is not for you to be arrogant in this. Get forth, for you are too, and you will be among the humiliated."
He said, “Respite me until the Day of Resurrection.”
He said: You are of the respited.
He said, “Because You have led me astray, I will surely guide you to a Straight Path.”
Then I will come to them from front of them and from behind them and from their right, and from their right, and from their left, and Thou wilt find no grace of them."
(Allah) said: "Get out from this (Hell), despised, disgraced, and whosoever follows them, I shall fill Hell with you all together."
And We said, "O Adam, dwell and dwell in the Garden and eat of it wherever you wish, but do not approach this tree, lest you become wrongdoers.”
Then Satan tempted them to reveal to them what he had given them, and he said to them, "Your Lord has not forbidden you this tree, lest you may become angels, or become angels.”
And he swore to them, "Indeed, I am your sincere-wisher."
Then he made them slip. Then when they tasted the tree, their shameful parts became apparent to them, and they began to cover the leaves of the Garden. And their Lord called out to them, "Did I not forbid you that tree, and I did not forbid you that tree? Indeed, he is an enemy to you."
They said, "Our Lord, we have wronged ourselves. If You do not forgive us and have mercy on us, You will surely have been lost."
He said, "Get down, one of you will be enemies. And you will have a dwelling in the earth and a temporary provision for a while.
He said, "Therein you will live, and therein will be it, and you will be brought forth from it.”
O Descendants of Adam! We have given you to cover your private parts, and the adornment of righteousness, and the raiment of righteousness. That is best for the people who understand.
O Children of Adam! Do not let Satan tempt you, as he expelled your parents from Paradise, stripping them their private parts, stripping them their private parts. And he sees you and his tribe, where you can see them. We have made the devils friends of those who do not believe.
And when they commit an indecency, they say, “We found our fathers doing, and Allah has commanded us.” Say, “God does not command His indecency. Do you attribute to God what you do not know?”
Say, "My Lord has commanded justice. So set your faces in every place of worship, and call your face to Him. Pray to Him, and pray to Him, and you will return to Him.
He has guided a guidance, and there has been a party of them. Indeed, they have taken guardians as patrons instead of God. They are the ones who have taken the right path.
O Children of Adam! Take your adornment every adornment, and eat and drink, and do not be wasteful. Indeed, He likes not the wasters.
Say, "Who has forbidden the adornment of Allah which He has provided for His servants and the good things which He has provided for His servants?" Say, "These are the present life in this life and the Day of Resurrection." Thus do We explain Our signs for a people who understand.
Say, "My Lord has forbidden indecencies, indecencies, and what is apparent to you, and sin, and unjustified aggression, and that which you associate with God has not sent down any sanction, and that you do not know anything of God, and that which you do not know.
For every nation there is an appointed term; when the term appointed, they cannot delay it, nor can they hasten it.
O Children of Adam, when there come to you messengers from among you, relating to you My verses, then those who fear God, and those who fear themselves, no fear shall be upon them, nor shall they grieve.
But those who reject Our revelations and treat them, they are the inmates of the Fire; therein they shall abide forever.
Who is more unjust than he who invents a lie against Allah, or denies His signs? Or shall they have a portion of the Book, until Our angels come to them, (saying), "Where are those whom you used to invoke besides God?" They will say, "We have forsaken us." They will say, "Yes, and we will bear witness against us."
He will say: "Enter the gates of Hell (Hell), and before those who passed away before you, and there is a group of those who passed away (from the Fire)." And when a group of them, they shall say: "Our Lord! We have led us astray, so that it will be the first of them." They will say: "Our Lord! We have led us astray, but the torment of the Fire will touch them." He will say: "It is a double provision."
And the first among them will say to the last of them: "You are not of us, but taste the punishment because of which you used to earn."
Indeed, those who reject Our revelations and turn away against them, the gates of Heaven shall not be opened for them, nor shall they enter Paradise until the camel passes through the needle. Thus do We recompense the wrongdoers.
For them is the bed of Hell, and We have prepared them over them. Thus do We recompense the wrongdoers.
As for those who believe and do good deeds, We shall not burden any soul except according to its capacity. These are the inhabitants of Paradise, where they will abide forever.
We shall strip their hearts into their hearts, and they will be admitted to gardens underneath which rivers flow, and they say: "All praise belongs to Allah." And if Allah had not guided us, We would not have guided it. Our Lord's Messengers will say, "We have no guidance. Our Lord's Messengers has brought the truth. This is the Garden which you used to do."
And the companions of the Garden will call out to the companions of the Garden: "We have found that which our Lord promised us." They will say, "We have found what your Lord promised you." They will say, "Yes, but the curse of your Lord will be the curse of the wrongdoers."
Those who bar the way of Allah and seek to make it crooked, and do not believe in the Hereafter.
And between them is a barrier, and on the day of the heights, every people will recognize them, and they will say, "Peace be to you! Peace be to you!" They will not be entered to them, and they will be asked.
